Atlantic was not just different but in many respects also objectionable. In America, utopia and dystopia seemed to live side by side, and Italian references to the United States were frequently in support of progressive or reactionary causes. Political thinkers including Cesare Balbo, Carlo Cattaneo, Giuseppe Mazzini, and Antonio Rosmini used the United States to shed light on the course of their nation's political resurgence. Concepts from Montesquieu, Rousseau, and Vico served to evaluate what Italians discovered about America. Ideas about American "domestic manners" were reflected and conveyed through works of ballet, literature, opera, and satire.Transcending boundaries between intellectual and cultural history, America in Italy is the first book-length examination of the influence of America's political formation on modern Italian political thought.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 08. Jul 2019) 0aIntellectualszItalyxHistoryy18th century. 0aIntellectualszItalyxHistoryy19th century. 0aPolitical sciencezItalyxHistoryy18th century. 0aPolitical sciencezItalyxHistoryy19th century. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Italy.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPUP eBook-Package 2016-2018z978311066259708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPUP eBook-Package 2017z978311063881308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPUP eBook-Package Pilot Project 2017z978311054332240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781400887811zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781400887811.jpg  a978-3-11-054332-2  PUP eBook-Package Pilot Project 2017b2017  a978-3-11-063881-3  PUP eBook-Package 2017b2017  a978-3-11-066259-7  PUP eBook-Package 2016-2018  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL